NOTE 15:	If the MS supports access to an SNPN providing access for localized services in SNPN, the UE ensures that such an SNPN is not inaccessible due to being in the list of "temporarily forbidden SNPNs for access for localized services in SNPN" when the validity information of the SNPN changes from not met to met. As a UE implementation option, the MS can remove an SNPN from the list of "temporarily forbidden SNPNs for access for localized services in SNPN" associated with the selected entry of the "list of subscriber data" or the selected PLMN subscription, when the validity information of the SNPN changes from not met to met.
